						<div class="postbody">Historically, a lot of old NROM games which don't use many tiles at the same time could easily have used a configuration like this if the idea would have ocurred to people. I imagine one 32kB ROM would be cheaper than 16kB+8kB back in the days, so that might have saved manufacturing costs slightly? Then again, it might not have mattered much compared to all other costs involved in making cartridge based games... especially in the NES market where the CIC was the biggest PITA...</div>

